claim.claim-text:
8. A method for making an elongated pressure actuated switch, comprising the steps of: 
a) providing a seamless tubular member fabricated from a resiliently flexible non-conductive polymeric resin, the tubular member having an inside wall defining a lengthwise extending axial bore; 
b) providing a fluid conductive coating composition comprising a polymeric binder, a particulate conductive filler; 
c) passing a quantity of the fluid conductive composition through the axial bore of the tubular member so as to coat the inside wall; 
d) drying the conductive composition to leave a non-fluid conductive layer on the inside wall; and, 
e) dividing the conductive layer into first and second separate spaced apart conductive electrode films.
